{"word":"σκληρός","slug":"σκληρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκληρός</b></el> <el>(σκληρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκέλλω'><el>σκέλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>hard</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>durus</el>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of sound, <i>hard, harsh, crashing</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>aridus</el>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>hard, stiff, unyielding</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>rigidus</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—of boys who look old for their age, <i>stiff, sturdy</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of things, <i>hard, austere, severe</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>σκληρὰ μαλθακῶς λέγων</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>σκληρῶς καθῆσθαι</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>on a hard seat</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}